.TH "drm_vblank_count_and_time" 9 "drm_vblank_count_and_time" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_vblank_count_and_time \- retrieve "cooked" vblank counter value and the system timestamp corresponding to that vblank counter value.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u64" drm_vblank_count_and_time
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pipe "  ","
.BI "ktime_t *vblanktime "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "pipe" 12
index of CRTC whose counter to retrieve
.IP "vblanktime" 12
Pointer to ktime_t to receive the vblank timestamp.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Fetches the "cooked" vblank count value that represents the number of
vblank events since the system was booted, including lost events due to
modesetting activity. Returns corresponding system timestamp of the time
of the vblank interval that corresponds to the current vblank counter value.

This is the legacy version of \fBdrm_crtc_vblank_count_and_time\fP.
